==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Oyez
<hw>O"yez`</hw> <pr>(⟦omac⟧"y⟦ecr⟧s`; 277)</pr>, <pos>interj.</pos>
<ety>[Anglo-F. <ets>oyez</ets> hear ye. See <er>Oyer</er>.]</ety>
<def>Hear; attend; -- a term used by criers of courts to secure silence
before making a proclamation. It is repeated three times.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>oyes</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oylet</ent>⟦br⟧
